  "coverage_note": "All principal dimensions (LOA, beam, draft, displacement, GT) are real, citable values from Wikipedia, builder/operator pages, and Ship-Technology. LBP is almost never published for these specialised offshore vessels - gap throughout except DLV 2000 (waterline length given). Depth published only for Thialf, Pioneering Spirit, plus keel-to-pedestal heights for Saipem 7000/Castorone. Block coefficient not published for any (semi-subs have no meaningful Cb) - gap throughout. Mass properties (LCG/VCG/TCG, displacement-condition breakdowns) are confidential proprietary ballast/design data and are NOT published - gap. Radii of gyration (kxx/kyy/kzz) are never published; emitted as estimated using standard naval-architecture relations (roll ~ fraction of beam; pitch/yaw ~ fraction of length) with the relation named; semi-subs use higher roll-gyradius fraction of beam. These must be replaced with model-test/ballast-book values before engineering use. Saipem and Boskalis brochure PDFs were binary-corrupt via fetch; corroborated by Ship-Technology and a maritime database. Subsea7 datasheet PDFs not fetched; values from search snippets and Ship-Technology.",
  "verdict": {
    "physically_plausible": true,
    "fabrication_suspected": true,
    "citations_check": "thin",
    "summary": "Dimensional/displacement/lift data is physically plausible and verifies well against sources for every spot-checked vessel (Sleipnir 220x102m/273,700t/2x10,000t, Pioneering Spirit 382x124m/48,000t topsides, Saipem 7000 198x87m/172,000t, Bokalift 2 231x49m/54,827t dwt, Castorone 330x39m). Gyradius values (kxx~0.35-0.40*B, kyy/kzz~0.25-0.30*L) are correctly flagged 'estimated' with sane methodology, and block coefficient/LCG/VCG/TCG/loading condition are honestly marked 'gap'. HOWEVER, fabrication is suspected in the vessel_id (IMO) field: 4 of 4 spot-checked IMO numbers are WRONG and are presented as hard facts WITHOUT being listed in any citation's fields array (except Bokalift 2, whose IMO is cited AND correct). Sleipnir actual IMO 9781425 (not 9806079); Thialf actual 8757740 (not 8757307); Saipem 7000 actual 8501567 (not 8757345); Castorone actual 9444194 (not 9522297). The two semi-sub crane vessels carry near-identical bogus '8757xxx' IMOs, a placeholder signature. Classic pattern: real cited dimensions + invented uncited identifiers. Secondary issues: Castorone builder listed 'Yantai Raffles hull / STX Korea outfit' vs sources citing Keppel Shipyard Singapore; Bokalift 2 hull builder given as generic '2000 hull' but actually Harland & Wolff Belfast (conversion-by-Boskalis is fine). Citations rated THIN: present and on-topic for dimensional fields and URLs are real/plausible, but key identifier fields (IMO) and several builder claims carry no supporting citation while stated as fact. The dataset was truncated mid-record in the final vessel (Seven Oceans), so completeness of that record is unverified.",
